Date: Fri, 28 Feb 2014 14:52:50 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 002/188] input: touchscreen: ti_am335x_tsc: Flush interrupts
 before suspend

This commit comes from branch ti-linux-3.12.y:
  git://git.ti.com/ti-linux-kernel/ti-linux-kernel.git

Previously, pending interrupts in tscadc were causing HW_PEN interrupt,
needed for wake from DS0, to get disabled immediately by IRQ handler
after being enabled. Flush all pending interrupts in suspend handler
before enabling HW_PENi interrupt so that this no longer happens and
board is able to wake from DS0 on a touch event.

Signed-off-by: Dave Gerlach <d-gerlach@ti.com>
Acked-by: Felipe Balbi <balbi@ti.com>
(cherry picked from commit 185a8852eb1c8a205895a37d8d2b6bd3bfaee834)
---
 drivers/input/touchscreen/ti_am335x_tsc.c |    3 +++
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/input/touchscreen/ti_am335x_tsc.c b/drivers/input/touchscreen/ti_am335x_tsc.c
index 6daa68a..4d7c28f 100644
--- a/drivers/input/touchscreen/ti_am335x_tsc.c
+++ b/drivers/input/touchscreen/ti_am335x_tsc.c
@@ -466,6 +466,9 @@ static int titsc_suspend(struct device *dev)
 
 	tscadc_dev = ti_tscadc_dev_get(to_platform_device(dev));
 	if (device_may_wakeup(tscadc_dev->dev)) {
+		/* Flush any pending interrupts */
+		titsc_writel(ts_dev, REG_IRQSTATUS, 0xffffffff);
+
 		idle = titsc_readl(ts_dev, REG_IRQENABLE);
 		titsc_writel(ts_dev, REG_IRQENABLE,
 				(idle | IRQENB_HW_PEN));
